de.luis.kioskComponents.ePayment

Class PaySession

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.luis.kioskComponents.ePayment.AbstractSession
      • de.luis.kioskComponents.ePayment.PaySession

  • public class PaySession
extends AbstractSession
    Project: LUIS ePayment

    PaySession is the first class to use in LUIS ePayment. It's the starting point to logon and receive a PayTerminal object for contacting the EFT.
    In a LUIS ePayment SharedTerminalServer environment, this class is substituted by PaySharedSession

    Version:
    $Revision: 1.57 $

    • Method Detail

      • login

        public PayTerminal login(PayConfiguration config)
                  throws PayException
        Authorisation method of LUIS ePayment and the EFT. The merchant PIN is part of the PayConfiguration object, which is passed as parameter. A login sends a logon command to the EFT and returns - if successfull - a newly created PayTerminal object. This PayTerminal object contains methods to invoke payments, refunds, reversals and all the additional administrative functions.
        Parameters:
        config - The PayConfiguration defines the way, how to communicate with the EFT.
        Returns:
        A newly created PayTerminal instance, if authentication succeeded.
        Throws:
        PayException - Every error results in a PayException or its devived classes.

      • initialStartup

        public PayResult initialStartup(PayConfiguration config)
                         throws PayException
        The initial startup method is an adminstrative function to initialise the EFT, set its TerminalID, its connection parameters to the network provider and more. Typically this method is not needed, because every EFT is initialized and connectly configured by the network provider before sending to the client. But if a re-initialization is needed, this method is mandatory.
        Not all EFTs support the configuration of all its internal settings. So this method might not be able to configure the EFT. In this case, the configuration has to be done via the EFTs own PINPad and function menue.
        Parameters:
        config - The PayConfiguration, which held all Parameters for the re-configuration of the EFT.
        Throws:
        PayException - Every error results in a PayException or its devived classes.

      • setLanguage

        public void setLanguage(PayConfiguration config,
                        java.lang.String language)
                 throws PayException
        Administrative function to define the language of the display texts in the EFT. It will be invoked during the call of initialSetup.
        Not all EFTs support this method.
        Parameters:
        config -
        language - A String defining the language of the EFT display texts. Possible values are {"en", "de", "fr", "it"}.
        Throws:
        PayException - Every error results in a PayException or its devived classes.
